<script>
function openPage(pageName,elmnt,color) {
  var i, tabcontent, tablinks;
  tabcontent = document.getElementsByClassName("tabcontent");
  for (i = 0; i < tabcontent.length; i++) {
    tabcontent[i].style.display = "none";
  }
  tablinks = document.getElementsByClassName("tablink");
  for (i = 0; i < tablinks.length; i++) {
    tablinks[i].style.backgroundColor = "";
  }
  document.getElementById(pageName).style.display = "block";
  elmnt.style.backgroundColor = color;
}

// Get the element with id="defaultOpen" and click on it
document.getElementById("defaultOpen").click();



</script>

Thank you for completing the Online Self-Paced Introduction and Overview. Please take a moment to review the training agenda and register for the sessions that best fit your needs. 




I. Approach

  • All users have real-time access to the online self-paced learning module to prepare for Hands-On-Training
  • TX3C Administrators focuses on local flexibility options
  • Workers level up each session
  • Workers gain access to UAT as a sandbox between sessions
  • Staggering allows workers to attend different functional areas
  • Weekly Office Hours allow workers to try things out before Q & A
  • No Drinking at the Firehose 

II. Online Training Center 

  • Available 24 x 7 
  • Reminder: this must be taken before taking the hands-on, instructor-led training (exception: Local Technical System Administration) 
  • Training Schedule Registration options are presented after completion of the self-paced course 


Please ensure that you can access the training site. If you are unable to access the site, please contact your IT. Some users may need to disable the VPN. https://trn.childcare.twc.texas.gov/KinderTrack/BaseWebPages/OtherPages/Login.aspx?ap=0

IV. Session Overviews 

Training Schedules Sessions Overview
TX3C Administration (2 hour sessions) 
Local Technical System Administration
  • Understand how to use various search fields to locate Operators efficiently.
  • Learn how to create new operators and configure details such as login information, roles, supervisors, and flags.
  • Learn how to update office locations
  • Warn, Prevent, Ignore Settings
Local WFS Board Management
  • Case Search
  • Case, Provider and Payment Overview
  • Alert Management
  • Manage Board District Settings 
  • Board Calendars (Board, Provider, Holidays)
  • RMR Rates (Board Max Rates) 
  • Quality Rates (Board Max Rates) 
  • Program / Funds Management
Worker Supervision
  • Sending Alerts 
  • Process Alerts 
  • Reassigning Workers 
  • Management Reports 
  • Deleting 
  • Audit Trails 
  • Private
Case Workers (2 hour session)
CM 101 Applications Intake
  • Waiting List (TWIST Converted)
  • New Applications
  • Referrals (WFCM and eventually DFPS)
  • Determining Eligibility
  • Authorizing Care
  • Notifying the Caregiver (Approved / Denied)
CM 102 Case Management
  • Monitoring Cases
  • Case Alerts
  • Making Case Changes
  • Case Change Notices
  • Notes
  • Attendance Monitoring and Updates
CM 103 Special Handling
  • DFPS Cases
  • Homeless
  • Initial Job Search
  • Activity Interruption
  • Changing Provider
  • Case Research
  • PSOC Incentives
Provider Workers
CCP 101 – Provider Data Management
  • Licensing Regulation Data Imports
  • Quality Ratings
  • Published Rates
  • Provider Agreement
  • Creating a Relative Provider
CCP -102 Family and Child Services
  • Reviewing Family
  • Reviewing Scheduled Payments
  • Sanctions
Payment  Workers
PAY 101 - Payment Calculations
  • Searching and Reviewing Legacy Payments
  • Program Funds and related Eligibility Types
  • Prospective Payment Cycle
  • Payment schedule in KinderTrack
  • Payment set-ups
    • Board Calendars
    • Family Schedules
    • Provider Rates
    • Quality Rates
PAY 102 - Subsidy Monitoring
  • How Payments are calculated
    • Provider Type
    • Market Rate
    • Published Provider Rates
  • Children in Care Processing Payments (status of payment)
  • Researching Payment
  • Checking for Attendance
PAY 103 - Adjustments
  • Making payment adjustments
    • Assigned to the wrong Provider
    • Correct scheduling end date
    • Changing a child's schedule status (full-time/part-time)
  • Levies
  • Adding Payments
